    "body": "`Cython.Compiler.ExprNodes.infer_sequence_item_type` infers a C numeric item type for tuple/list literals composed of function arguments annotated as `T | None` (or `Optional[T]`), even though those references can be `None` at runtime. The inferred C type then propagates into a generator expression's loop variable, producing C code that calls `__Pyx_PyFloat_AsDouble(Py_None)`\r\n\r\n## Minimal reproducer\r\n\r\n```python\r\n# repro.pyx\r\ndef synchronous_gc(\r\n    total_size: float | None = None,\r\n    min_last_access: float | None = None,\r\n    max_object_size: float | None = None,\r\n):\r\n    assert sum(\r\n        1 for x in (total_size, min_last_access, max_object_size) if x is not None\r\n    ) < 2\r\n    return \"ok\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nCompile and call:\r\n\r\n```python\r\n>>> import repro\r\n>>> repro.synchronous_gc()\r\nTraceback (most recent call last):\r\n  ...\r\nTypeError: must be real number, not NoneType\r\n```\r\n\r\nGenerated C (relevant lines, Cython 3.2.5):\r\n\r\n```c\r\ndouble __pyx_v_x;                                  /* <-- loop variable typed as C double */\r\n...\r\n__pyx_t_4 = __Pyx_PyFloat_AsDouble(__pyx_t_3);     /* <-- fails when __pyx_t_3 is Py_None */\r\nif (unlikely((__pyx_t_4 == (double)-1) && PyErr_Occurred())) __PYX_ERR(...);\r\n__pyx_cur_scope->__pyx_v_x = __pyx_t_4;\r\n__pyx_t_3 = PyFloat_FromDouble(__pyx_cur_scope->__pyx_v_x);\r\n```\r\n\r\nExpected: `__pyx_v_x` should be `PyObject *` because the tuple items may be `None`.",
    "closed_at": null,
